===== TEST confirm of val-selected candidate (SGD lam=10) =====
>>> [test sgd] ewc_er lam=10 (val-selected)   acc=0.7152  forget=0.2461
    vs class-IL test ER 0.7226  ->  -0.0074   (the +0.0071 val bump flipped to -0.0074 on test)

================================================================================================
VERDICT
  task-IL : ER ~ EWC ~ EWC+ER, all at ceiling. Combining is a wash (head competition removed).
  class-IL: EWC+ER does NOT beat ER at any lambda.
            - Adam: no lambda beats ER (best -0.0075).
            - SGD : best val lambda=10 is a noise-level +0.007 on val that FLIPS to -0.007 on test.
            - The earlier -0.088 (lam=1e3) was purely a mis-set lambda; the right lambda recovers to
              ~ER but never past it.
  Mechanism: on class-IL replay owns the shared-head bottleneck; the EWC anchor pins old-task weights
  and at best gets out of replay's way (~ER), never adds to it. Consistent with pt2/pt3: replay is
  the only lever; weight-space regularisation adds ~0 on top. (1 seed; buffer=1000.)
================================================================================================
